<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-07T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.4193/107: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-07T17:00:00+09:00">September 7, 1937—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 7—6:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>356. Our 327, August 29, 9 p.m., wounding of British Ambassador to
                                China.</p>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>Provisional Japanese reply was handed yesterday to British
                                    Embassy and is to the effect that up to the present
                                    investigations have failed to produce any evidence that the
                                    shooting was done by a Japanese plane and that consequently it
                                    is still impossible to determine whether the responsibility
                                    rests with Japan.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>As text has been given to the press I shall not cable it
                                    unless instructed.</item>
                            </list>
                            <p>Repeated to Shanghai for relay to Nanking.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>